---
name: deploy-ingest-worker
description: Deploy the WatchLater ingest-worker Bun service to a Linux VPS over SSH. Run after the user has established an SSH session.
---

You are deploying the `ingest-worker` service from this repo to a Linux VPS.
The worker is a Bun HTTP server at `ingest-worker/` in the watchlater repo.
It listens on a configurable PORT, exposes `POST /ingest` and `GET /health`.

## Step 1 — Orient

Find out where you are and what's available:

```bash
whoami && uname -a && cat /etc/os-release | grep PRETTY
which bun || echo "bun not installed"
which git || echo "git not installed"
ls ~/ingest-worker 2>/dev/null || echo "not deployed yet"
```

Report OS, whether Bun and git are present, and whether a previous deploy exists.

## Step 2 — Install Bun (if missing)

```bash
curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash
source ~/.bashrc
bun --version
```

## Step 3 — Get the code onto the server

**Option A — git clone (preferred if repo is public or SSH key is set up):**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/sahilsinghM/watchlater.git ~/watchlater
```

**Option B — if already cloned, pull latest:**
```bash
cd ~/watchlater && git pull
```

After cloning, symlink the worker dir for convenience:
```bash
ln -sfn ~/watchlater/ingest-worker ~/ingest-worker
```

## Step 4 — Install dependencies

```bash
cd ~/ingest-worker && bun install
```

## Step 5 — Set environment variables

Create the env file. Ask the user for any values not already known:

```bash
cat > ~/ingest-worker/.env << 'EOF'
INGEST_SECRET=REPLACE_WITH_RANDOM_SECRET
SUPABASE_URL=REPLACE_WITH_SUPABASE_URL
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_SB_SECRET_KEY  # sb_secret_... only; legacy JWT keys are disabled
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_OPENROUTER_KEY
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4.1-mini
PORT=3001
EOF
```

Generate a strong random secret if one isn't provided:
```bash
openssl rand -hex 32
```

Remind the user: **do not commit `.env` to git**.

## Step 6 — Smoke-test before daemonising

```bash
cd ~/ingest-worker && bun run src/index.ts &
sleep 2
curl -s http://localhost:3001/health
kill %1
```

Expected response: `{"ok":true}`. If it fails, check the output for errors before continuing.

## Step 7 — Create a systemd service

```bash
sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/ingest-worker.service > /dev/null << EOF
[Unit]
Description=WatchLater ingest-worker
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=$(whoami)
WorkingDirectory=$HOME/ingest-worker
EnvironmentFile=$HOME/ingest-worker/.env
ExecStart=$(which bun) run src/index.ts
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable ingest-worker
sudo systemctl start ingest-worker
```

## Step 8 — Verify the service

```bash
sudo systemctl status ingest-worker
curl -s http://localhost:3001/health
```

Both should succeed. If the service is not active, run:
```bash
sudo journalctl -u ingest-worker -n 50 --no-pager
```
and report the error.

## Step 9 — Open the firewall port (if ufw is active)

```bash
sudo ufw status
sudo ufw allow 3001/tcp
```

If ufw is inactive, skip this step. Also check Hetzner's Cloud Firewall in the dashboard — port 3001 must be open for inbound TCP.

## Step 10 — Get the public URL

```bash
curl -s https://api.ipify.org
```

The worker URL is `http://<PUBLIC_IP>:3001`.

Report the full URL to the user and remind them to set these two env vars in Vercel:

```
INGEST_WORKER_URL=http://<PUBLIC_IP>:3001
INGEST_WORKER_SECRET=<the secret from Step 5>
```

Then redeploy Vercel (git push or trigger from the dashboard).

## Step 11 — End-to-end check

Once Vercel is redeployed, the user should test with a real YouTube video at
`watchlater-sigma.vercel.app`. The processing page should show real step
progress (fetching_metadata → reading_transcript → generating_lesson → ready)
instead of the fake animation, confirming the worker is being called.
